<emphasis box="[164,286,198,219]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="762">Discussion</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="39.[164,779,198,434]" pageId="39" pageNumber="762">
<bibRefCitation author="Barrientos JA &amp; Febrer JB" box="[164,514,228,250]" pageId="39" pageNumber="762" pagination="121 - 129" refId="ref81119" refString="Barrientos JA, Febrer JB. 1986. Aranas de Menorca. I. Agelenidae (Araneae). Description del macho de Malthonica balearica Brignoli, 1978. Orsis 2: 121 - 129." type="journal article" year="1986">Barrientos &amp; Febrer (1986)</bibRefCitation>
suggested that this species is closely related to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Simon" baseAuthorityYear="1870" box="[525,612,260,281]" class="Arachnida" family="Agelenidae" genus="Eratigena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="39" pageNumber="762" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="picta">
<emphasis box="[525,612,260,281]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="762">E. picta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The generic assignment of this species was controversial until the restricted definition of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1898" box="[442,572,320,341]" class="Arachnida" family="Agelenidae" genus="Malthonica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="39" pageNumber="762" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[442,572,320,341]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="762">Malthonica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Barrientos JA &amp; Cardoso P" pageId="39" pageNumber="762" pagination="59 - 68" refId="ref81088" refString="Barrientos JA, Cardoso P. 2007. The genus Malthonica Simon, 1898 in the Iberian Peninsula (Araneae: Agelenidae). Zootaxa 1460: 59 - 68." type="journal article" year="2007">Barrientos &amp; Cardoso (2007)</bibRefCitation>
